CURL IOTA Addresses not transitioned by September 2017

At the beginning of August, the IOTA foundation decided to switch from their own CURL hashing scheme, to KERL, which is basically Keccak in trinary. The wallet included a transitioning tool to make it easy for users (with help by some extra code in the iri node codebase) to switch from their old CURL addresses to new KERL addresses.

As detailed in this forum post, in September the IOTA foundation decided to end this transition period. Untransitioned IOTA would have to go through the same reclaim process as IOTA claimed due to key reuse.

If you find your old CURL addresses here, you will have to use the claim process include in wallet 2.5.2 or later. After claiming, wait for further instructions from the IOTA foundation.

Claim processing has started now. Addresses marked in bold below require KYC before claims can be processed (see this blog post).
